    <title>Steam, Epic and GMG are canceling Ghost of Tsushima PC pre-orders in non-PSN countries</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Screenshot from Ghost of Tsushima showing a character overlooking a field, with hills and mountains in the background." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ydpUm-5qwgcVccbLngiYvVzt0Vs=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73341722/Ghost_of_Tsushima_Director_s_Cut_Wallpaper.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Screenshot: &lt;em&gt;Ghost of Tsushima&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="052Lal"&gt;Steam, Epic, and Green Man Gaming are reportedly canceling and refunding preorders of the PC port of &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/6/24092291/ghost-of-tsushima-directors-cut-pc-release-date-steam"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ghost of Tsushima&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for buyers who live in over 170 countries without PlayStation Network access, &lt;a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/ghost-of-tsushima-directors-cut-pc-players-are-getting-auto-refunds-if-they-cannot-legally-sign-up-for-psn"&gt;reports &lt;em&gt;Eurogamer&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. That’s despite the fact that arguably the most important part of the game is still playable without PlayStation Network account linking. The news comes after Valve &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/games/2024/5/10/24153281/uhhh-anything-you-want-to-tell-us-about-ghost-of-tsushimas-psn-requirement-on-pc-sony"&gt;abruptly delisted the game in those countries yesterday&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="Pxvu7m"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ghost of Tsushima &lt;/em&gt;only requires PSN account linking for its Legends multiplayer mode, a requirement the single player campaign is exempt from, the game’s developer went out of its way &lt;a href="https://x.com/SuckerPunchProd/status/1786462939748384943"&gt;to say in a recent post&lt;/a&gt;. Steam, Green Man Gaming, and Epic Games Store each had disclaimers noting the same thing. In theory,...&lt;/p&gt;
