  &lt;p id="CrMGYr"&gt;The &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/5/28/23738770/right-to-repair-updates-laws"&gt;right-to-repair movement&lt;/a&gt; has logged some serious wins &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23951200/right-to-repair-law-apple-ifixit-iphone"&gt;over the past several years&lt;/a&gt;, with states like &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/5/28/23738770/right-to-repair-updates-laws#stream-entry-cedcdb35-6e12-4ebc-9909-e3cbe9b58147"&gt;California&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2022/6/3/23153504/right-to-repair-new-york-state-law-ifixit-repairability-diy"&gt;New York&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/5/24/23736326/minnesota-right-to-repair-laws-passed-electronics-free-documentation"&gt;Minnesota&lt;/a&gt; having recently passed laws that make it easier for consumers to repair their own devices. But being able to obtain parts and manuals is only part of the process — you also need the tools. Luckily, &lt;strong&gt;iFixit’s Pro Tech Toolkit &lt;/strong&gt;is on sale at &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01GF0KV6G/?tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://howl.me/cmdQFzLKRan"&gt;Best Buy&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifixit.com%2Fproducts%2Fpro-tech-toolkit&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F5%2F11%2F24153242%2Fifixit-pro-tech-toolkit-sharge-retro-67-charger-deal-sale" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;iFixit&lt;/a&gt; for $59.96 ($15 off), matching the lowest price we’ve seen on the versatile tool set.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="c-float-left c-float-hang"&gt;&lt;aside id="W9bx4V"&gt;&lt;div data-anthem-component="readmore" data-anthem-component-data='{"stories":[{"title":"The EU’s new right-to-repair rules make companies fix your device after a warranty expires","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/23/24138499/eu-new-right-to-repair-rules-fix-after-warranty-expire"},{"title":"Apple will open the iPhone to repair with used parts","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/11/24127278/apple-iphone-repair-used-parts"},{"title":"The Verge’s 2024 Mother’s Day gift guide","url":"https://www.theverge.com/24115101/best-mothers-day-gift-ideas-2024-mom-tech-gadgets"}]}'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/aside&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="ZMPYWR"&gt;Chances are you know iFixit for its in-depth teardowns of various gadgets and gizmos, including &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/25/23888952/ifixit-iphone-15-pro-max-teardown-repairability"&gt;iPhone 15 Pro Max&lt;/a&gt;, headsets like the &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/3/24059966/ifixit-apple-vision-pro-teardown-video"&gt;Apple Vision Pro&lt;/a&gt;, and the confounding mess that is the &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifixit.com%2FNews%2F95474%2Frabbit-r1-and-humane-ai-pin-teardown-the-beginning-of-a-new-device-category&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F5%2F11%2F24153242%2Fifixit-pro-tech-toolkit-sharge-retro-67-charger-deal-sale" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Humane AI Pin&lt;/a&gt; (sorry not sorry). That said, the company also...&lt;/p&gt;
